Sulfur mustard (military designation HD or H) is a blister agent (vesicant) that causes severe
Sulfur mustard damages cells within minutes of contact
the onset of pain and other health effects is delayed until hours after exposure
Large exposures to sulfur mustard may be fatal
Sulfur mustard is also an alkylating agent that damages the cells within the bone marrow that are necessary for making blood cells
this affects the body’s immune system
sulfur mustard also affects a part of the nervous system responsible for everyday bodily function
causing “cholinergic toxicity,” marked by excessive saliva
Sulfur mustard has been used as a chemical warfare agent to cause delayed casualties
It has an odor of garlic
odor is not a reliable indicator of sulfur mustard and should not be depended on to warn of sulfur mustard exposure.
